  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180°C.",
    "Pat the roast dry with paper towels.",
    "Rub the roast with olive oil and sea salt, pressing salt into the meat.",
    "Tie rosemary, thyme, bay leaves, and crushed garlic into a bouquet garni with kitchen twine.",
    "Place the roast on a rack in a roasting pan and lay the bouquet garni around it.",
    "Pour red wine and beer into the pan to keep the meat moist.",
    "Roast for 1 hour 30 minutes, basting occasionally with pan juices.",
    "Increase oven temperature to 220°C for the last 15 minutes to crisp the crust.",
    "Let the roast rest for 15 minutes before slicing."
